>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":66.66} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Clean and disinfect</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Clean AND disinfect&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prepare/cleaning-disinfection.html\">frequently touched surfaces</a>&nbsp;daily</strong>. This includes tables, doorknobs, light switches, countertops, handles, desks, phones, keyboards, toilets, faucets, and sinks.</li><li><strong>If surfaces are dirty, clean them:</strong>&nbsp;Use detergent or soap and water prior to disinfection.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#e2e2e2\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e2e2e2\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>To disinfect:</strong><br>Most common EPA-registered household disinfectants will work. Use disinfectants appropriate for the surface.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Options include:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Diluting your household bleach.</strong><br>To make a bleach solution, mix:<ul><li>5 tablespoons (1/3rd cup) bleach per gallon of water<br>OR</li><li>4 teaspoons bleach per quart of waterFollow manufacturers instructions for application and proper ventilation. Check to ensure the product is not past its expiration date. Never mix household bleach with ammonia or any other cleanser. Unexpired household bleach will be effective against coronaviruses when properly diluted.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Alcohol solutions.<br></strong>Ensure solution has at least 70% alcohol.</li><li><strong>Other common EPA-registered household disinfectants.</strong><br>Products with<a href=\"https://www.epa.gov/sites/production/files/2020-03/documents/sars-cov-2-list_03-03-2020.pdf\">EPA-approved emerging viral pathogenspdf icon[7 pages]external icon</a>claims are expected to be effective against COVID-19 based on data for harder to kill viruses. Follow the manufacturers instructions for all cleaning and disinfection products (e.g., concentration, application method and contact time, etc.).</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->','How to Protect Yourself','','inherit','closed','closed','','962-revision-v1','','','2020-03-23 22:42:23','2020-03-23 22:42:23','',962,'https://live-crisis-response.pantheonsite.io/2020/03/23/962-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(969,1,'2020-03-23 23:14:27','2020-03-23 23:14:27','<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":66.66} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:66.66%\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Call your doctor:</strong>If you think you have been exposed to COVID-19 and develop a fever and symptoms, such as cough or difficulty breathing, call your healthcare provider for medical advice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column {\"width\":33.33} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:33.33%\"><!-- wp:image {\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/images/COVIDweb_10_temperature_1.png\" alt=\"\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"verticalAlignment\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns are-vertically-aligned-center\"><!-- wp:column {\"verticalAlignment\":\"center\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-center\"><!-- wp:button -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\" href=\"https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/symptoms.html\">Symptoms</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- 